### [Genesis Chapter 24](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#001.md)

[Genesis 24:1](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">gen 24:1</span></span>

And Abraham

The entire chapter is highly typical:

\(1\) Abraham, type of a certain king who would make a marriage for his
son ([Mat 22:2](../../../bib/kjv/mat022.htm#002).md); ([Joh
6:44](../../../bib/kjv/joh006.htm#044).md).

\(2\) the unnamed servant, type of the Holy Spirit, who does not "speak
of himself," but takes of the things of the Bridegroom with which to win
the bride ([Joh 16:13](../../../bib/kjv/joh016.htm#013).md); ([Joh
16:14](../../../bib/kjv/joh016.htm#014).md).

\(3\) the servant, type of the Spirit as enriching the bride with the
Bridegroom's gifts ([Gal 5:22](../../../bib/kjv/gal005.htm#022).md); ([Co1
12:7-11](../../../bib/kjv/co1012.htm#007).md).

\(4\) the servant, type of the Spirit as bringing the bride to the
meeting with the Bridegroom ([Act
13:4](../../../bib/kjv/act013.htm#004).md); ([Act
16:6-7](../../../bib/kjv/act016.htm#006).md); ([Rom
8:11](../../../bib/kjv/rom008.htm#011).md); ([Th1
4:14-16](../../../bib/kjv/th1004.htm#014).md).

\(5\) Rebekah, type of the Church, the ecclesia, the "called out" virgin
bride of Christ ([Gen 24:16](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#016).md); ([Co2
11:2](../../../bib/kjv/co2011.htm#002).md); ([Eph
5:25-32](../../../bib/kjv/eph005.htm#025).md).

\(6\) Isaac, type of the Bridegroom, "whom not having seen," the bride
loves through the testimony of the unnamed Servant ([Pe1
1:8](../../../bib/kjv/pe1001.htm#008).md).

\(7\) Isaac, type of the Bridegroom who goes out to meet and receive His
bride ([Gen 24:63](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#063).md); ([Th1
4:14-16](../../../bib/kjv/th1004.htm#014).md).

