[Genesis 24:66](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#066.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_066">gen 24:66</span></span>

servant This is the model servant:

\(1\) he does not run unsent, ([Gen
24:2-9](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#002).md).

\(2\) goes where he is sent, ([Gen
24:4](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#004).md); ([Gen
24:10](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#010).md).

\(3\) does nothing else;

\(4\) is prayerful and thankful, ([Gen
24:12-14](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#012).md); ([Gen
24:26](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#026).md); ([Gen
24:27](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#027).md).

\(5\) is wise to win, ([Gen 24:17-18](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#017).md);
([Gen 24:21](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#021).md).

Compare ([Joh 4:7](../../../bib/kjv/joh004.htm#007).md).

\(6\) speaks not of himself, but of his master's riches and Isaac's
heirship, ([Gen 24:22](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#022).md); ([Gen
24:34-36](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#034).md); ([Act
1:8](../../../bib/kjv/act001.htm#008).md).

\(7\) presents the true issue, and requires clear decision, ([Gen
24:49](../../../bib/kjv/gen024.htm#049).md).

